Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.27,0:00:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, under the Roman Republic,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.31,0:00:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the tribes occupied the important government offices.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.44,0:00:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In Rome there was a clear difference between the two castes:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.90,0:00:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the nobles, called the "patricians",
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.95,0:00:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8\i1}I'm bored.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.32,0:00:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and the common folk and farmers, called the "plebs".
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.79,0:00:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The two consuls, the dictator and the three hundred senators
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.42,0:00:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,were all chosen from the ranks of the nobles.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.09,0:00:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The Senate was the highest institute of legislation,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.80,0:00:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and the popularity of the Sena—
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.84,0:00:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.84,0:00:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that Mr. Omichi from Class A?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.43,0:00:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say so.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.39,0:00:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It really is Class A. I wonder what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.11,0:00:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows? I guess Omichi is just going nuts again.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.71,0:01:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is that... Chitanda?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.88,0:01:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.68,0:01:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's continue with the class.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.35,0:01:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Where was I again?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.89,0:01:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, the Senate.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.14,0:01:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The Senate was the highest institute of legislation...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.90,0:01:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{OP}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.77,0:01:34.24,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,250)}Bored, sitting on the windowsill,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.24,0:01:42.37,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,250)}I frown at the wind to hide my awkwardness
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.58,0:01:50.46,Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(280,0)\blur3\t(0,989,2,\blur0.5)}Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.46,0:01:55.55,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,250)}I nod uncertainly as I shape
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.88,0:02:01.26,OP,,0,0,0,,the future in my hands feeling mighty
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.26,0:02:06.43,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,250)}I feel that the wind is bringing change
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.81,0:02:11.52,OP,,0,0,0,,I guess that's your fault for calling out to my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.27,0:02:18.61,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,250)}The cloudy sky tells a tale of what's to come
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.61,0:02:27.12,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,0)}Spread our wings with more courage than ever before
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.12,0:02:31.71,OP,,0,0,0,,Light and dark are still vague in the distance
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.71,0:02:38.01,OP,,0,0,0,,but still we want to know the reason behind kindness
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.01,0:02:42.55,OP,,0,0,0,,No one so far has ever reached
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.55,0:02:45.43,OP,,0,0,0,,the shining distance far beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.43,0:02:54.02,OP,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,350)}Let's get there before the past takes it all
