Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.08,0:12:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Kawasaki clearly had trouble with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.96,0:12:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Which made sense,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.09,0:12:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,because we hadn't even covered range in class yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.05,0:12:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Kawasaki said he didn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.59,0:12:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The teacher got angry when he heard that and started railing at us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.85,0:12:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The next person he called was Tamura, who's really good at math,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.90,0:12:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,but he didn't know either.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.32,0:12:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That was when I realized that he'd forgotten where our class was up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.53,0:12:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The others realized it too, and the classroom got a bit noisy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.83,0:12:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The teacher got even angrier and launched into a harsh tirade.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.04,0:12:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.17,0:12:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,he kept hitting the blackboard as if to punctuate his rant.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.42,0:13:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I think there were people in my class who could've solved the problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.38,0:13:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but everyone kept quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.09,0:13:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he called Tamura again, told him to stand up and started yelling at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.02,0:13:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's when I stood up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.77,0:13:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked him to double-check where we were up to in the curriculum.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.98,0:13:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Right,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.77,0:13:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that's when I got angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.95,0:13:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.82,0:13:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he looked at his book,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.12,0:13:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,mumbled "Oh, I see," and a few words of apology,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.79,0:13:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,told Tamura to sit down, and the rest of the class went on as normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.38,0:13:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He's that kind of teacher, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.59,0:13:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't even imagine how much trouble he caused me after the midterms!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.01,0:13:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We had teachers like him in elementary and junior high too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.72,0:13:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not a bad teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.10,0:13:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And your poor grades aren't his fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.98,0:13:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Try to shape up before finals.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.31,0:14:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's my story. What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.69,0:14:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What's strange about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.95,0:14:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, I wanted to ask you why he'd make a mistake like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.58,0:14:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He's usually a lot more careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.38,0:14:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.71,0:14:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Omichi is hard on his students, but he's hard on himself as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.43,0:14:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So why would he make such a mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.39,0:14:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.97,0:14:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither do I.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.10,0:14:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oreki!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.14,0:14:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.93,0:14:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to know, go ask him if you can take a look inside his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.98,0:14:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I would've done that already if I could!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.02,0:14:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.57,0:14:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Better give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.61,0:14:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can't stop thinking about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.53,0:14:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You should think about it as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.49,0:14:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.24,0:14:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I just know you'll be able to figure it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.79,0:15:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Get rid of that can-do attitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.71,0:15:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point expecting so much from him, Chi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.38,0:15:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a grasshopper in his previous life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.05,0:15:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Mayaka, you know about people's past lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.38,0:15:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That got her attention! Good one, Ibara!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.97,0:15:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But right now, I'm still wondering about today's class.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.60,0:15:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Dammit. There's no shaking her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.52,0:15:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stop thinking about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.57,0:15:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I often see him writing in his notebook after class.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.49,0:15:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you think he does that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.61,0:15:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he must be noting down where the class is up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.41,0:15:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.74,0:15:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why he double-checks which class is written on the sign beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.62,0:15:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounds like a foolproof system, so how could he have made that mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.13,0:15:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If he's taking notes,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.34,0:15:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I suppose he'd write something like "Page 15, 1st July, Class A".
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.55,0:15:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Otherwise, he'd forget where they were up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.56,0:16:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What if he just read the wrong day's entry?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.10,0:16:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he'd revisit old material, not something new.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.61,0:16:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Use your brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.27,0:16:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.65,0:16:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mind if I ask you something?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.99,0:16:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.61,0:16:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand why you'd get angry,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.37,0:16:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,but even then you wouldn't normally speak out against a teacher like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.91,0:16:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So why'd you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.87,0:16:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I got angry,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.54,0:16:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but I don't think it was because of how mean he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.05,0:16:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, was it because the students who could've solved it stayed quiet too?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.97,0:16:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,No,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.51,0:16:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think anyone would have volunteered at a time like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.51,0:16:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, was it because no one else told him that he was wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.85,0:16:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.48,0:16:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be because you felt sorry for Tamura?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.03,0:16:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I did feel sorry for him,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.32,0:16:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,but that wouldn't have made me angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.82,0:16:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, it'd be understandable for a teacher to tell off a student
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.45,0:17:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,who didn't seem to have learned anything from the previous class.{from the teacher's point of view}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.33,0:17:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't know why I got angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.84,0:17:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to analyze myself like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.55,0:17:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.88,0:17:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What makes Chitanda angry, and what makes her happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.89,0:17:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't know her well enough to judge that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.35,0:17:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Oreki?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.27,0:17:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Omichi probably does take notes of the class's progress in his book.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.19,0:17:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And yet, he still made a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.91,0:17:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He was ahead of the class,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.82,0:17:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}which means there must have been a note saying the class
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.03,0:17:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}was up to a page further on in the textbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.54,0:17:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Your class hasn't studied range yet, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.63,0:17:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.50,0:17:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What if you actually had?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.51,0:17:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.55,0:18:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Omichi teaches math every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.51,0:18:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Last year's 1-A must've learned it by this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.31,0:18:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sadly, simply getting the year wrong won't cut it as an explanation here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.77,0:18:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.23,0:18:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The teachers are issued new textbooks every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.40,0:18:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They need to keep up with any minor changes made to the students' editions, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.36,0:18:22.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Omichi is using the fourth edition, which was published this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.70,0:18:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.41,0:18:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a real cornucopia of useless facts, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.58,0:18:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, call me a database.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.50,0:18:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What if Omichi took so many notes that he simply got them mixed up?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.51,0:18:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No, Chitanda wouldn't believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.22,0:18:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't understand this "range" thing either, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.98,0:18:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a hard enough time just writing {\i1}x{\i0} and {\i1}y{\i0} on a plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.19,0:18:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd have a pretty hard time if Omichi called me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.99,0:18:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.49,0:19:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Class D's already learning about range?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.82,0:19:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.70,0:19:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So Satoshi's class is already up to range,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.04,0:19:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}but not Chitanda's class or mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.50,0:19:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.25,0:19:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Your face says you figured something out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.59,0:19:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.22,0:19:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Chitanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.05,0:19:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.68,0:19:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We can say for sure that there was a note specifying a later page in the book.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.39,0:19:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.81,0:19:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know that the note related to the progress of a class from this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.94,0:19:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.{goddamn individually wrapped biscuits}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.94,0:19:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, what if the note wasn't about your class at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.57,0:19:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What if it was meant to record the progress of Satoshi's class?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.08,0:19:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,My class?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.12,0:19:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Omichi is teaching classes A, B, C, and D.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.79,0:19:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Just because it wasn't A or B,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.17,0:19:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean it had to be D.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.46,0:20:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's so special about D?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.01,0:20:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't be surprised if he mistook D for A.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.47,0:20:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way you could mistake the letter C for an A, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.23,0:20:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? You're just talking nonsense again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.36,0:20:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You couldn't mistake the letter D for an A either.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.73,0:20:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Omichi is a math teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.86,0:20:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.74,0:20:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,A math teacher would be more likely to mistake the letter D for A.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.62,0:20:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.33,0:20:50.97,signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5\c&H636364&\fnThrow My Hands Up in the Air\pos(997,522)}Oreki Houtarou's drawing
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.79,0:20:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say Omichi wrote "Page 10, 1st July, A" and "Page 15, 1st July, D"...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.13,0:20:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What if he did?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.30,0:20:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,There's still no room for mistake there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.47,0:20:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If he got the A and D confused, that would explain it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.56,0:20:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It would, but how could he?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.97,0:20:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Because a math teacher would write them like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.02,0:21:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, he'd write A and D in lowercase!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.86,0:21:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.57,0:21:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.16,0:21:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I lost marks on my English exam because the teacher couldn't tell them apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.83,0:21:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? You too, Mayaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.12,0:21:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Though, it was N and H for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.29,0:21:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. That's definitely possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.75,0:21:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I guess that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.47,0:21:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,A and D...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.22,0:21:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't blame him for getting them confused.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.47,0:21:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I was too harsh on him, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.23,0:21:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in the wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.19,0:21:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh, why do you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.73,0:21:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He{\i0} was in the wrong! You were right to tell him off!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.28,0:21:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,To begin with, you're—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.44,0:21:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.70,0:21:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's already rather late.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.32,0:21:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we get going?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.95,0:21:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But, Fuku!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.12,0:21:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Mayaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.74,0:21:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The mystery's been solved, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.45,0:21:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.71,0:21:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Fuku!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.17,0:22:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Chitanda got angry despite herself,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.46,0:22:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and wanted to know the reason why.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.05,0:22:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Despite what she said before about anger not being a bad thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.34,0:22:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in truth, she doesn't want to get angry herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.64,0:22:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Houtarou, Chiatanda, let's get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.93,0:22:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She wanted to know why
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.85,0:22:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}because she believed there must have been a reason for Omichi's anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.39,0:22:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Right, I'll tidy up!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.48,0:22:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and wanted to consider her own anger to be her fault alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.94,0:22:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's the kind of thing Chitanda Eru would do, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.11,0:22:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Nah,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.12,0:22:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}what do I even know about Chitanda in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.29,0:22:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even if I can predict what she'll do,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.42,0:22:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I can't actually figure out what's going on in her head.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.25,0:22:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I know what this is all about.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.21,0:22:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}One of the seven deadly sins...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.84,0:22:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.93,0:22:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I gotta remember to be more careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.10,0:22:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How many times has she surprised me
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.39,0:22:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}just in this one day?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.35,0:22:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Oreki!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.02,0:23:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you going home?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.73,0:23:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, right. I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.57,0:23:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oreki,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.57,0:23:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.32,0:23:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You're always helping me out with my troubles.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.08,0:23:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if only someone could help me with mine...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.37,0:23:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you two doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.54,0:23:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you coming as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.88,0:23:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we're leaving now!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.30,0:23:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.47,0:23:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll just deal with the rest tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.93,0:23:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oreki!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.64,0:23:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{sa}That's true for you, Mayaka, but think about it for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.86,0:23:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And thus, another day of my high school life was wasted.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.74,0:23:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}As for my deadly sins,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.78,0:23:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}sloth is more than enough for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.70,0:23:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{ED}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.79,0:24:07.55,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,300)\blur2}Let us meet in a blissful dream tonight, let it be our love
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.55,0:24:11.55,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,200)\blur2}Find me, I beg you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.55,0:24:16.64,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,350)\blur2}We promised to meet, drifting in and out of sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.03,0:24:37.78,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,200)\blur2}This sprouting warmth confuses us
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.87,0:24:48.71,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,150)\blur2}Don't you understand this feeling yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.30,0:24:54.80,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,150)\blur2}Normally such random glances hold no meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.80,0:25:00.14,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,450)\blur2}Isn't it the same when making friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.14,0:25:05.90,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,150)\blur2}The little shooting stars we wish upon, vanishing into the dawn
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.90,0:25:10.86,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,150)\blur2}are a magic that only unfolds in the night
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.86,0:25:17.66,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,150)\blur2}Let us meet in a blissful dream tonight, let it be our love
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.66,0:25:21.66,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,150)\blur2}Find me, I beg you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.66,0:25:26.62,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,350)\blur2}We promised to meet, drifting in and out of sleep
